reviews.review_text:
Wonderful audience recording There is a solid contingent of folks out there who will swear to you that audience-sourced shows trump SBDs.  I think this tape is evidence that they may be on to something.  A really shining example of how good late-80's AUD recordings could sound, when made by a good taper.  On this one, you can really hear all the nuances of the arena, and you get a great idea of what it sounded like to be in the crowd for one of these performances.  THe olny flaw is a very small amount of high-end "fuzz" -- discernable through headphones, but perhaps not otherwise.

Performance-wise, it seems that the band took a while to warm up on this MSG run.  I'm really not a fan of the set they did the night before this one, and don't think they really started to hit their stride until the second set the night AFTER this one.  In the meantime, we get a solid, if not inspired, set on this night.  Highlights are a great PITB > UJ and a nicely done "All Along The Watchtower."  The rest is what I would consider fairly average 1988 fare.
